<h2 id="how-to-embed-a-gallery">How to embed a gallery</h2>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">{% include gallery %}</code> lets you easily embed a gallery into your post. To use the gallery-includeâ€¦</p>

<h3 id="step-1">Step 1</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Make two images: a thumbnail and a big image.</li>
  <li>Name the thumbnail <em>gallery-image-thumb.jpg</em> andâ€¦</li>
  <li>â€¦name the big <em>gallery-image.jpg</em>.</li>
  <li>Place them in the <em>images</em>-folder.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="step-2">Step 2</h3>

<p>Define the big version in frontmatter,</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gallery:
    - image_url: gallery-image.jpg
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>If you like captions, give each image a caption:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gallery:
    - image_url: gallery-image.jpg
       caption: Starting Page with huge One Logo
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="step-3">Step 3</h3>

<p>Add the include whereever you want in your content with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">{% include gallery %}</code>.</p>

<div class="alert-box info "><p>Have a look at this example-entry. And have a look into the images-folder. :)</p>
</div>

